main event: Ground-radar observation of an unidentified object over Kindly Air Force Base, Bermuda on September 5, 1959.
interesting points: The object was observed on radar for 10 minutes and 45 seconds.
The object was observed at an elevation of 270 degrees.
The object appeared to be solid and made no sound.
The object was observed after an initial 30-minute alarm.
No further observation or reports were made after the initial sighting.
